OL,7,FThe couple had to pay significant sums
OL,8,Fback to the Post Office, causing them
OL,9,Fsevere financial hardship.
OL,11,FMr Riddell said: "When we complained
OL,12,Fto them they turned around and said we
OL,13,Fwere the only one. They said that all
OL,14,Fthe time.
OL,16,F"They said we had to put the money in.
OL,17,FWe scrimped and saved. Every month we
OL,18,Fhad to put money in with no
OL,19,Fexplanation as to where it had gone.
OL,20,FThe Post Office had all the stuff, it
OL,21,Fwas horrendous.
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}        G6/13
