OL,7,F"It got to the stage where Carol was
OL,8,Fso fed up she closed the shop for a
OL,9,Fweek and was still no further. She was
OL,10,Fsuspended and I took over. I was
OL,11,Fsuspended. Carol had to go down for
OL,12,Fmeetings. It was just horrendous. We
OL,13,Fsaid we had to get out or we're going
OL,14,Fto be dead.
OL,16,F"Carol was mortified when they said
OL,17,Fthey were going to prosecute. You were
OL,18,Fa criminal according to them, you were
OL,19,Fguilty before you were proven
OL,20,Finnocent."
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}        G7/13
